    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="983"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d983">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–1954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d983fn1">Handwritten notation on the source text indicates
                        that the Secretary of State saw this telegram.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-19T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 19, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 665. For Secretary from Under Secretary.
                    Reference: <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 568.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d983fn2">Dated July 18, <ref target="#pg_1436">p. 1436</ref>.</note>
                    In event failure Geneva conference I believe it would be useful if President
                    included in his radio and TV speech reference to approach British and ourselves
                    have made to prospective members of southeast Asia collective security
                    organization (<gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 660<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d983fn3">Dated July 19, <ref target="#pg_1448">p. 1448</ref>.</note>
                    and previous).</p>
                <p>If you agree suggest you send us text of pertinent language so that I may inform
                        <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> before speech delivered.</p>
                <p>I told <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes-France</persName> today of the
                    President’s intention. He expressed interest and I invited his suggestions for
                    anything he thought might be usefully included in the speech. He promised to let
                    me know.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
